The Vercel AI SDK supports multiple AI providers through a standardized adapter pattern. This task adds a new fictional `@ai-sdk/pixelart` provider that **only supports image generation** (no text, chat, or embeddings). It follows the same patterns as existing providers like `@ai-sdk/fal` and integrates with the `ImageModelV3` interface from `@ai-sdk/provider`.

The provider will hit `https://api.pixelart.ai/v1` and expose provider-specific settings (`size`, `style`, `pixelDensity`) via the `providerOptions.pixelart` object.

---

## Key Reference Files

- `packages/fal/package.json` — package.json template to copy
- `packages/fal/tsconfig.json` — tsconfig template to copy
- `packages/fal/tsconfig.build.json` — build tsconfig template
- `packages/fal/tsup.config.ts` — tsup build config template
- `packages/fal/vitest.node.config.js` — vitest node config template
- `packages/fal/vitest.edge.config.js` — vitest edge config template
- `packages/fal/src/version.ts` — VERSION export pattern
- `packages/fal/src/fal-image-model.ts` — image model implementation pattern
- `packages/fal/src/fal-provider.ts` — provider factory pattern
- `packages/fal/src/index.ts` — index exports pattern
- `packages/provider/src/image-model/v3/image-model-v3.ts` — `ImageModelV3` interface
- `packages/provider/src/image-model/v3/image-model-v3-call-options.ts` — `ImageModelV3CallOptions`

---

